@node "INSTALL" "SN AutoUL v1.1 - Installation Procedures"
@toc "MAIN"
┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN AutoUL v1.1 - Installation Procedures
└──────────────────────────────────────────┘

 1  Run the included installation script either of the following
    two ways:

    a.  Type "Installer Install_AutoUL" from the Shell.

    b.  Click on the "Install_AutoUL" icon from Workbench.

 2  The installation script moves the required files to your specified
    location, including adding a CNet help file called "UL."

 3  Somewhere in the middle of the "3: Main prompt" items in bbsmenu,
    with your favorite editor, change "UL, User List" to the following:
    "CNETUL, User List"  (It is important that you change to this
    exactly.  If you don't, this won't work unless you edit my program.)

 4  At the bottom of the "3; Main prompt" items in bbsmenu, add the
    following line:  (say you placed SN_AutoUL in PFiles:)

    UL  |{#0PFiles:SN_AutoUL}
         ^
      CTRL-Q

 5  Reload your bbstext/bbsmenu via CNet's Control Panel menu (option
    #3, "Text/menu reload  RAmiga-T" and you're all set!

 6  Now everytime someone asks for a UL, they'll get a much more user
    friendly menu to deal with...

───SN/AHI (910) 326-3804 (28.8k)─────────────────────────────────────────
